%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20startup%20wants%20to%20build%20the%20world's%20largest%20cargo%20plane%20big%20enough%20to%20carry%20wind%20turbines%20the%20size%20of%20a%20football%20field%20%E2%80%94%20take%20a%20look%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221869%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Radia%20WindRunner%20in%20a%20field%20surrounded%20by%20wind%20turbines.%20It%20is%20unloading%20a%20giant%20turbine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6605c65b3f923f7dab0258a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221402%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERadia%20wants%20to%20ship%20giant%20turbines%20around%20the%20world%20via%20a%20behemoth%20cargo%20plane%20called%20WindRunner.%3Cp%3ERadia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERadia%2C%20a%20Colorado-based%20startup%2C%20wants%20to%20build%20the%20world's%20largest%20cargo%20plane.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBilled%20the%20WindRunner%2C%20the%20plane's%20sole%20purpose%20is%20to%20carry%20oversized%20wind%20turbine%20blades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20aims%20to%20deliver%20turbine%20blades%20that%20are%20difficult%20to%20ship%20by%20ground.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Colorado-based%20startup%20wants%20to%20build%20the%20world's%20largest%20cargo%20plane%20that's%20about%20the%20length%20of%20a%20football%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20sole%20purpose%3A%20to%20deliver%20giant%20wind%20turbine%20blades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradia.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERadia%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20founded%20in%202016%20by%20MIT-educated%20rocket%20scientist%20Mark%20Lundstrom%20%E2%80%94%20says%20it%20wants%20to%20usher%20in%20the%20next%20phase%20of%20wind%20energy%20by%20solving%20a%20logistics%20problem%20attached%20to%20installing%20larger%20wind%20turbines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETall%20turbine%20towers%20with%20bigger%20blades%20can%20harness%20more%20energy%20since%20they%20can%20take%20better%20advantage%20of%20the%20faster%20wind%20speeds%20available%20at%20high%20altitudes.%20But%20the%20bigger%20the%20blades%2C%20the%20harder%20they%20are%20to%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObstructions%20such%20as%20highway%20overpasses%2C%20power%20lines%2C%20bridges%2C%20and%20tunnels%20create%20a%20logistics%20nightmare%20for%20the%20delivery%20of%20each%20blade.%20Radia%20says%20today's%20roads%20can%20%26quot%3Bbarely%20support%26quot%3B%20the%20blades%20stretching%20230%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221836%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rendering%20of%20a%20truck%20transporting%20a%20large%20wind%20turbine%20blade.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6605c60516bde8d4ead3585f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22918%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20rendering%20visualizes%20one%20of%20the%20obstacles%20of%20transporting%20a%20large%20wind%20turbine%20blade%20by%20ground.%3Cp%3ERadia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERadia%20said%20this%20won't%20get%20any%20easier%20over%20time%20as%20future%20blades%20are%20expected%20to%20stretch%20more%20than%20330%20feet%20and%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20feasible%20to%20move%20on%20current%C2%A0infrastructure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20fully%20constructed%2C%20a%20blade%20cannot%20be%20bent%20or%20folded%2C%20limiting%20both%20the%20route%20a%20truck%20can%20take%20and%20the%20radius%20of%20turns%20that%20it%20can%20make%2C%20often%20making%20elongated%20routes%20necessary%20to%20avoid%20urban%20roadblocks%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Office%20of%20Energy%20Efficiency%20and%20Renewable%20Energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadia's%20giant%20cargo%20plane%2C%20called%20the%20WindRunner%2C%20hopes%20to%20fly%20over%20those%20barriers.%20The%20company%20says%20in%20press%20release%20materials%20that%20it%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20plane%20that's%20356%20feet%20long%2C%20has%20a%20wingspan%20of%20261%20feet%2C%20and%20is%2079%20feet%20tall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20comparison%2C%20before%20it%20was%20destroyed%20by%20Russia%20in%202022%2C%20the%20behemoth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantonov-an-225-mriya-worlds-largest-cargo-plane-history-details-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAntonov%20An-225%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Soviet-era%20cargo%20plane%20also%20used%20to%20carry%20over-sized%20loads%20such%20as%20wind%20turbine%20blades%20%E2%80%94%20was%20about%20276%20feet%20long%2C%20had%20a%20wingspan%20of%20290%20feet%2C%20and%20was%20about%2060%20feet%20tall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Antonov%20AN-225%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6605c6121caec1275a6a9b7c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGLEB%20GARANICH%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantonov-an-225-mriya-worlds-largest-cargo-plane-history-details-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20An-225's%20cargo%20volume%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%2046%2C000%20cubic%20feet%2C%20and%20it%20could%20carry%20about%20550%2C000%20lbs%20of%20freight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadia's%20plane%20has%20a%20cargo%20bay%20volume%20of%20272%2C000%20cubic%20feet%20%E2%80%94%2012%20times%20that%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F50th-anniversary-boeing-747-queen-of-the-skies-passenger-flight-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoeing%20747-400F%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20maximum%20payload%20weight%20capacity%20of%20160%2C000%20lbs%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20size%20advantage%20will%20allow%20for%20the%20carrying%20of%20the%20more-than-300-foot-long%20blades%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20loaded%20through%20a%20nose%20door%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20building%20of%20more%20profitable%20onshore%20turbines%2C%20Radia%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20accessibility%2C%20Radia%20said%20the%20WindRunner%20will%20operate%20from%20regional%20hubs%20where%20the%20blade%20turbines%20are%20imported%20or%20produced%2C%20and%20deliver%20them%20directly%20to%20wind%20farms%20by%20landing%20on%20%26quot%3Ba%206%2C000-foot%20semi-prepared%20dirt%20or%20gravel%20landing%20strip%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20allow%20WindRunner%20to%20land%20at%20%26quot%3Balmost%20any%20commercial%20airport%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Radia%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20aircraft%20is%20designed%20with%20a%20range%20of%201%2C200%20miles%20at%20its%20maximum%20payload%20and%20a%20cruising%20altitude%20of%2041%2C000%20feet.%20It%20can%20cruise%20at%20Mach%200.6%2C%20or%20about%20460%20mph.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22WindRunner%20taxi%20drawing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6605d5763f923f7dab0269b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConcept%20drawing%20of%20the%20WindRunner%20taxiing.%3Cp%3ERadia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20result%20will%20be%20highly%20efficient%20wind%20energy%20at%20enormous%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20Radia%20CEO%20Mark%20Lundstrom%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20business%20perspective%2C%20that%20means%20that%20the%20onshore%20wind%20industry's%20internal%20rate%20of%20return%20will%20double%2C%20attracting%20much%20more%20capital%20to%20renewables.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Radia%2C%20it%20is%20more%20than%20halfway%20through%20its%20estimated%20eight-year%20process%20to%20design%2C%20build%2C%20and%20certify%20the%20mammoth%20WindRunner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Radia%20did%20not%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWindRunner%20joins%20the%20lucrative%20oversized%20cargo%20market%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERadia%20joins%20the%20niche%20network%20of%20%3Ca%20href%