0the%20world%20is%20on%20the%20precipice%20of%20seeing%20flexible%20schedules%20normalized%20in%20the%20next%20five%20to%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20early%2C%20knee-jerk%20resistance%20by%20CEOs%20and%20work%20devotees%20has%20softened%20in%20recent%20years%20and%20transformed%20from%20outright%20objection%20to%20cautious%20curiosity%20about%20how%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-introduced-4-day-week-struggled-to-switch-from-5-days-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshorter%20workweek%20might%20function%20in%20practice.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20haggling%20over%20logistics%20rather%20than%20debating%20philosophy%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.4dayweek.com%2Falex-pang%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlex%20Soojung-Kim%20Pang%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BWork%20Less%20Do%20More%3A%20Designing%20the%20Four%20Day%20Week%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20to%20that%20stage%20you%20haven't%20won%20completely%2C%20but%20you're%20now%20on%20grounds%20where%20a%20four-day%20week%20can%20be%20taken%20seriously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20brief%20history%20of%20the%20four-day%20workweek%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20a%20four-day%20workweek%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2023%2F12%2Fhow-to-actually-execute-a-4-day-workweek%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematerialized%20in%20the%201960s%20and%20early%201970s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20Pang%2C%20who%20serves%20as%20director%20of%20research%20at%204-day%20Week%20Global%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%20that%20helps%20facilitate%20large-scale%20trials%20of%20shorter%20workweeks%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20early%20experiments%20were%20done%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20industry%20to%20cut%20costs%20by%20decreasing%20factory%20operating%20hours.%20But%20those%20efforts%20were%20eventually%20killed%20off%20by%20the%20oil%20crisis%20and%20subsequent%20economic%20downturn%2C%20as%20well%20as%20growing%20resistance%20from%20labor%20unions%20who%20were%20concerned%20about%20longer%20days%2C%20according%20to%20Pang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20shorter%20workweeks%20went%20largely%20dormant%20until%20around%202016%20and%202017%2C%20when%20the%20movement%20once%20again%20started%20gaining%20steam%2C%20spurred%20on%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-working-to-live-rather-than-living-to-work-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGen%2520Z%2520is%2520choosing%2520to%2Cof%2520work%2520told%2520Business%2520Insider.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyounger%20generations%20in%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20millennials%20reaching%20their%2030s%20by%20this%20point%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20this%20the%20way%20their%20parents%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Pang%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20a%20sense%20that%20there's%20an%20opportunity%20to%20fix%20what's%20broken.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20buzz%20around%20a%20shorter%20workweek%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-successful-trial-evidence-productivity-retention-revenue-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecame%20a%20certified%20boom%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20The%20shift%20to%20remote%20work%20forced%20people%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20a%20future%20of%20work%20that%20might%20look%20different%20than%20the%20past%2C%20Pang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20shifting%20worldview%20is%20what%20inspired%20Phil%20McParlane%2C%20a%20developer%20in%20Scotland%2C%20to%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F4dayweek.io%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4dayweek.io%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20job%20board%20exclusively%20for%20positions%20with%20flexible%20schedules%2C%20in%202020%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20told%20BI.%20The%20site%20advertises%2