vents%20of%20'Pathaan%202%2C'%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20a%20cinematic%20clash%20of%20titans.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Spring%20mania'%20impacts%20people%20with%20bipolar%20disorder%20and%20can%20be%20life-threatening.%20A%20therapist%20shared%20how%20she%20preps%20for%20the%20season%20every%20year.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Spring%20flowers%20in%20a%20field%20as%20the%20sun%20sets%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660473de16bde8d4ead2ca7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Ethethomsn%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPeople%20with%20bipolar%20disorder%20may%20experience%20%26quot%3Bspring%20mania%26quot%3B%20between%20winter%20and%20summer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChanges%20in%20daylight%20and%20circadiam%20rhythm%20can%20trigger%20manic%20episodes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20therapist%20shared%20the%20warning%20signs%2C%20and%20how%20sleep%20and%20structure%20help%20mitigate%20symptoms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUshering%20in%20warmer%20weather%20and%20brighter%20evenings%2C%20spring%20is%20often%20synonymous%20with%20optimism%20and%20peacefulness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20some%20people%2C%20the%20season%20can%20trigger%20the%20opposite%20feelings.%20People%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fbipolar-symptoms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebipolar%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20%26quot%3Bspring%20mania%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20manic%20episodes%20in%20the%20springtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cstcounseling.com%2Four-therapists%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClaudia%20Skowron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20licensed%20clinical%20professional%20counselor%20in%20Illinois%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20people%20with%20bipolar%20disorder%20oscillate%20between%20manic%20and%20depressive%20episodes.%20She%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbipolar-disorder-forced-me-to-drop-out-of-college-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanic%20episodes%3C%2Fa%3E%20typically%20last%20a%20week%20or%20longer%20and%20are%20characterized%20by%20%26quot%3Bracing%20thoughts%2C%20decreased%20need%20for%20sleep%2C%20impulsivity%2C%20grandiose%20thinking%2C%20irritability%2C%20and%20rapid%20speech.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20spring%20can%20trigger%20manic%20episodes%20in%20people%20with%20bipolar%20disorder%20is%20because%20they're%20more%20sensitive%20to%20light%20and%20circadian%20rhythm%20shifts%2C%20Skowron%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20do%20we%20begin%20to%20get%20more%20daylight%20naturally%20just%20due%20to%20the%20Earth's%20rotation%2C%20but%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20US%2C%20we%20also%20have%20daylight%20savings%2C%20which%20adds%20an%20additional%20hour%20of%20daylight%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20this%20actually%20really%20happens%20rather%20quickly%20and%20creates%20this%20misalignment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaylight-savings-time-dst-death-heart-attacks-accident%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edaylight%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20impacts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fend-daylight-saving-time-not-in-line-circadian-rhythm-doctors-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20people's%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Skowron%20said%20the%20symptoms%20in%20people%20with%20bipolar%20disorder%20can%20be%20extra%20heightened.%20She%20shared%20the%20signs%20to%20watch%20out%20for%2C%20as%20well%20as%20how%20she%20preps%20her%20clients%20and%20colleagues%20for%20the%20season%2C%20which%20she%20said%20lasts%20from%20mid-March%20through%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20risks%20include%20life-threatening%20behavior%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESkowron%20said%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%20for%20a%20patient%20is%20suicide%2C%20because%20there's%20%26quot%3Bactually%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20manic%20episodes%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20suicidality%20in%20the%20springtime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManic%20episodes%20trigger%20impulsivity%2C%20and%20patients%20who%20are%20not%20properly%20medicated%20or%20in%20therapy%20are%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20attempting%20suicide.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20kind%20of%20the%20part%20that%20we%20have%20to%20look%20out%20for%20most%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkowron%20said%20she%20has%20a%20very%20collaborative%20relationship%20with%20the%20psychiatrists%20who%20work%20with%20her%20patients%2C%20and%20that%20there's%20sometimes%20a%20%26quot%3Btemporary%20increase%26quot%3B%20in%20medications%20around%20springtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20she%20starts%20to%20notice%20symptoms%20in%20a%20patient%2C%20she%20might%20bump%20up%20their%20sessions%20to%20twice%20a%20week%20for%20the%20time%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatients%20learn%20to%20spot%20the%20warning%20signs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20defenses%20against%20spring%20mania%20is%20noticing%20your%20patterns%2C%20Skowron%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20a%20past%20history%20of%20springtime%20struggles%2C%20there's%20a%20pretty%20good%20chance%20that%20this%20can%20happen%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20a%20person%20has%20a%20history%20of%20impulsive%20behavior%2C%20she%20might%20ask%20them%20to%20make%20a%20list%20of%20any%20changes%20they're%20experiencing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbipolar-disorder-music-creative-outlet-mental-health-resource-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAre%20they%20going%20to%20bed%20later%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Do%20they%20have%20a%20sudden%20burst%20of%20energy%3F%20These%20check-ins%20can%20help%20them%20%26quot%3Bstay%20ahead%20of%20the%20curve%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fbipolar-disorder-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20treatment%20before%20an%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20clients%20who%20experience%20spring%20mania%20every%20year%2C%20Skowron%20helps%20them%20come%20up%20with%20a%20plan%20to%20mitigate%20symptoms.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20that%20is%20a%20vacation%2C%20maybe%20that%20is%20investing%20into%20another%20hobby%20to%20direct%20that%20energy%20into%20something%20else%20that%20can%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESleep%20and%20structure%20are%20key%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20reduce%20symptoms%20around%20the%20springtime%2C%20Skowron%20said%20she%20stresses%20a%20consistent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgood-sleep-routine-avoid-burnout-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20routine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSleep%20is%20a%20key%20player%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20mood%20disorders%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20crucial%20to%20create%20healthy%20sleep%20routines%20%E2%80%94%20going%20to%20bed%20at%20the%20same%20time%20each%20night%2C%20waking%20up%20at%20the%20same%20time%20each%20morning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommends%20that%20patients%20invest%20in%20supplements%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fmelatonin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emelatonin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20blackout%20curtains%2C%20or%20a%20good%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Flunya-sleep-mask-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep%20mask%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20they%20have%20trouble%20fallin