0Narasimha%20Rao.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Bihar%20Chief%20Minister%20Karpoori%20Thakur%20and%20agronomist%20MS%20Swaminathan%20were%20also%20conferred%20with%20the%20country's%20highest%20civilian%20award.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20government%20announced%20five%20names%20for%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20this%20year%2C%20which%20also%20included%20BJP%20leader%20LK%20Advani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20that%20President%20Murmu%20will%20pay%20a%20visit%20to%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20LK%20Advani's%20residence%20and%20confer%20him%20with%20the%20prestigious%20award.%20This%20was%20decided%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ailing%20health%20of%20the%20veteran%20BJP%20leader%20Advani%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20PM%20Charan%20Singh's%20award%20was%20received%20by%20his%20grandson%2C%20Jayant%20Singh%2C%20and%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao's%20award%20was%20received%20by%20his%20son%2C%20PV%20Prabhakar%20Rao.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMS%20Swaminathan's%20daughter%2C%20Nitya%20Rao%2C%20received%20the%20award%20for%20her%20father%20and%20Karpoori%20Thakur's%20award%20was%20received%20by%20his%20son%2C%20Ram%20Nath%20Thakur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20BJP%20National%20President%20JP%20Nadda%2C%20Congress%20leader%20and%20LoP%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20were%20present%20among%20other%20leaders%20on%20the%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%20June%2028%2C%201921%2C%20in%20Karimnagar%2C%20Telangana%2C%20being%20an%20agriculturist%20and%20an%20advocate%2C%20Narsimha%20Rao%20joined%20politics%20and%20held%20some%20important%20portfolios.%20He%20was%20the%20Minister%20of%20Law%20and%20Information%2C%201962-64%3B%20Law%20and%20Endowments%2C%201964-67%3B%20Health%20and%20Medicine%2C%201967%20and%20Education%2C%201968-71%2C%20Government%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%20He%20was%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20from%201971-73%20and%20General%20Secretary%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Congress%20Committee%20from%201975-76.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrained%20as%20a%20plant%20geneticist%2C%20Swaminathan's%20significant%20contributions%20to%20India's%20agricultural%20sector%20have%20earned%20him%20a%20reputation%20as%20the%20scientific%20leader%20of%20India's%20green%20revolution%20movement.%20His%20work%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20the%20agricultural%20renaissance%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20Karachi%2C%20in%20present-day%20Pakistan%2C%20on%20November%208%2C%201927%2C%20LK%20Advani%20has%20served%20as%20the%20President%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20for%20the%20longest%20period%20since%20its%20inception%20in%201980.%20Capping%20a%20parliamentary%20career%20of%20nearly%20three%20decades%2C%20he%20was%2C%20first%2C%20the%20Home%20Minister%20and%2C%20later%2C%20the%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20the%20cabinet%20of%20Shri%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20(1999-2004).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarpoori%20Thakur%20was%20born%20in%201924%20in%20one%20of%20the%20most%20backward%20sections%20of%20society%2C%20the%20Nai%20Samaj.%20He%20was%20a%20remarkable%20leader%20whose%20political%20journey%20was%20marked%20by%20his%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20the%20marginalised%20sections%20of%20society.%20He%20served%20as%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20Bihar%20and%20was%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20the%20struggle%20against%20social%20discrimination%20and%20inequality.%20His%20commitment%20to%20affirmative%20action%20gave%20representation%20and%20opportunities%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20oppressed%2C%20exploited%20and%20deprived%20sections%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChaudhary%20Charan%20Singh%20was%20born%20in%201902%20at%20Noorpur%20in%20Meerut%20district%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20in%20a%20middle%20class%20peasant%20family.%20He%20shifted%20to%20Meerut%20in%201929%20and%20later%20joined%20the%20Congress.%20He%20was%20first%20elected%20to%20the%20UP%20Legislative%20Assembly%20in%201937%20from%20Chhaprauli%20and%20represented%20the%20constituency%20in%201946%2C%201952%2C%201962%20and%201967.%20He%20became%20Parliamentary%20Secretary%20in%20Pandit%20Govind%20Ballabh%20Pant's%20Government%20in%201946%20and%20worked%20in%20various%20departments%20such%20as%20Revenue%2C%20Medical%20and%20Public%20Health%2C%20Justice%2C%20Information%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%201951%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20Cabinet%20Minister%20in%20the%20State%20and%20given%20charge%20of%20the%20Departments%20of%20Justice%20and%20Information.%20Later%2C%20he%20took%20over%20as%20the%20Minister%20for%20Revenue%20and%20Agriculture%20in%20the%20Cabinet%20of%20Sampurnanand%20in%201952.%20When%20he%20resigned%20in%20April%201959%2C%20he%20was%20holding%20charge%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Revenue%20and%20Transport.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711785420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fpsb9sfd_bharat-ratna-2024-twitter_625x300_30_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpresident-droupadi-murmu-confers-bharat-ratna-on-lk-advani-narasimha-rao-3-others-5338540%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20today%20conferred%20Bharat%20Ratna%20on%20five%20eminent%20personalities%2C%20including%20two%20former%20Prime%20Ministers%2C%20Chaudhary%20Charan%20Singh%20and%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpresident-droupadi-murmu-confers-bharat-ratna-on-lk-advani-narasimha-rao-3-others-5338540%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Kangana%20Ranaut's%20majestic%20Manali%20House%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711785295000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fms